.sp 1


	
      .RE
      .PP
\fB\-path\fR \fIpattern\fR
.RS 4

	
	
	  True if the object path matches
\fIpattern\&.\fR
The evaluation is done according to shell pattern matching rules\&.

	
      .RE
      .PP
\fB\-print\fR
.RS 4

	
	
	  Evaluates to TRUE \- used to print out the path and name of the object\&.

	
      .RE
      .PP
\fB\-regex\fR \fIpattern\fR
.RS 4

	
	
	  True if the object path matches
\fIpattern\&.\fR
Pattern evaluation is done using Regular Expression matching\&.

	
      .RE
      .PP
\fB\-size\fR \fI[>/</=]size\fR
.RS 4

	
	
	  True if the size of the object is within the range specified\&. NOTE: for combs, extrudes, and other composite objects this filter considers
\fIonly\fR
the object definition itself, not its related elements\&.

	
      .RE
      .PP
\fB\-stdattr\fR
.RS 4

	
	
	  Returns TRUE if an object has ONLY standard attributes associated with it\&. Standard attributes in BRL\-CAD are:
.sp
.it 1 an-trap
.nr an-no-space-flag 1
.nr an-break-flag 1
.br
